                <h1>What does it take to serve the Class of 2020? The Chronicle went behind the scenes at Marketplace</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/5a8e1dcd-d268-4de4-abca-06e6ae291342.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="&lt;p&gt;Executive&#x20;sous&#x20;chef&#x20;Todd&#x20;Dumke&#x20;said&#x20;that&#x20;he&#x20;tries&#x20;to&#x20;buy&#x20;local&#x20;food&#x20;for&#x20;Marketplace.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            <p>Executive sous chef Todd Dumke said that he tries to buy local food for Marketplace.</p>

                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/likhitha-butchireddygari">Likhitha Butchireddygari</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">November 7, 2016 | 12:11am EST</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2016/11/what-does-it-take-to-serve-the-class-of-2020-the-chronicle-went-behind-the-scenes-at-marketplace" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2016/11/what-does-it-take-to-serve-the-class-of-2020-the-chronicle-went-behind-the-scenes-at-marketplace&amp;text=What does it take to serve the Class of 2020? The Chronicle went behind the scenes at Marketplace" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="twitter" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
                                                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="mailto:?subject=What%20does%20it%20take%20to%20serve%20the%20Class%20of%202020%3F%20The%20Chronicle%20went%20behind%20the%20scenes%20at%20Marketplace%20|%20The%20Chronicle&amp;message=Check%20out%20this%20article%20from%20The%20Chronicle%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukechronicle.com%2Farticle%2F2016%2F11%2Fwhat-does-it-take-to-serve-the-class-of-2020-the-chronicle-went-behind-the-scenes-at-marketplace" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="email" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" onclick="window.print()" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fas fa-print"></i></a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                
                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>Marketplace is a staple of first-year life&mdash;but very few know what it takes to feed East Campus.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Marketplace offers three meals a day during the week and two on the weekend&mdash;brunch and dinner. Last Spring, Duke Dining transitioned from Bon Appétit Management Company, which provides food service to universities across the country, to a self-operating system,  hiring Mark Turner as executive chef and Todd Dumke as executive sous chef. Both said that they are committed to serving the type of students Duke attracts, whom Turner described as "coming from affluent families."</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <p>“They've traveled well. They understand food. They've eaten probably all over the world," Turner said. "I think their expectations are a little bit higher than some of the places that I've been to. We try to meet that expectation with quality food that's produced properly.”</p>
<p><strong>Writing the menu</strong></p>
<p>Dumke said that in creating Marketplace's menu, the chefs&nbsp;worked with nutritionists and considered students' allergies. </p>
<p>Marketplace staff meets with first-years dealing with severe allergies at the beginning of the year to discuss accommodation. It also has a strict no-nut policy, Turner stressed.</p>
<p>Turner has to ensure that the menu is logistically possible for Marketplace’s equipment and staff while also being creative. </p>
<p>“I don't just want to come in here and do another chef's food,” Turner said. “It's important to me that I have my mark on this operation and that my chefs get to flex their culinary skill and be involved with the creativity of the menu.”</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
        <div id="azk5125"></div>
<!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
                        </div>

                                                                            <p>Ultimately, he explained that there is a level of uncertainty with writing any menu. </p>
<p>“It's just an educated guess on what food you're going to use. It takes a lot of experience to understand that,” Turner said. “It's guesswork. There's no formula for it.”</p>
<p><strong>Sustainability</strong></p>
<p>Dumke also said that Marketplace has been working to improve sustainability. For example, they only use recyclable packaging. </p>
                            
    
<div class="mc-signup my-4 p-4 text-center " id="mc-container" data-mc="c4087a59c7">
    <h3>Get The Chronicle straight to your inbox</h3>
    <p>Signup for our editorially curated, weekly newsletter. Cancel at any time.</p>
